eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 40 Years
Maximum age: 80 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.
Known central nervous system (CNS) tumor involvement or metastases.

Patients with brain metastases are allowed provided that:
* No leptomeningeal disease is present
* Intracranial disease is controlled by prior local therapies (craniotomy, stereotactic radiosurgery, whole brain irradiation), as evidenced by brain MRI 4 weeks post treatment indicating no new intracranial disease
* Stable or decreasing dose of steroids provided patient on =< 20 mg of prednisone or its equivalent daily
Total bilirubin > 2 x institutional upper limit of normal (ULN) (unless documented Gilbert’s syndrome)
Malignant B cells must co-express CD5 with CD19 or CD20
Had received a hematopoietic stem cell transplant (HSCT) within the previous 90 days

Cardiac ejection fraction ≥50%, and QTcF<450 ms (males) or <470 ms (females) on ECG
             at Baseline.
Women who have defective DNA mismatch repair and are microsatellite instability positive (MSI+ and MSI-low)

MDS classified as follows: refractory anemia with excess blasts (RAEB)-1 (5%-9% bone marrow [BM] blasts); RAEB-2 (10%-19% BM blasts); chronic myelomonocytic leukemia (CMML) (5%-19% BM blasts); refractory anemia with excess blasts in transformation (RAEB-t) (20%-29% BM blasts) AND/OR by International Prognostic Scoring System (IPSS): intermediate-1 and high risk patients

Subjects may have received bevacizumab, VEGF-Trap, or other VEGF blocking tyrosine
             kinase inhibitors, provided that they did not progress while receiving one of these
             agents. Subjects may not have previously received pazopanib.

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Safety of PLX3397 in combination with paclitaxel will be assessed by reported adverse events; and the results of physical examinations, vital signs, ECGs, hematology and serum chemistry laboratory values.

outcome_measures.measure: Characterization of the safety profile of SAR302503, including the frequency, duration, and severity of adverse events (AEs) 2 years

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Induction: pre-infusion (0 hr) on Day 1 of Cycle 1; pre-infusion (within 5 hr prior to dose) on Day 1 on Cycles 2, 4; Post-induction: at treatment discontinuation (up to Month 24); 120 days and 1-2 years post-last dose (maximum up to 5 years) (infusion duration: 90 minutes) (1 cycle: 21 days)
outcome_measures.time_frame: Pre-infusion (0 hr) on Day 1 of Cycle 1 up to maximum 5 years. Detailed timeframe is given in outcome measure description.
